info.title: ApiManagementClient
info.description: Use these REST APIs to get the analytics reports associated with your Azure API Management deployment.

parameters.name: resourceGroupName
parameters.description: The name of the resource group.

parameters.name: serviceName
parameters.description: The name of the API Management service.

parameters.name: $filter
parameters.description: The filter to apply on the operation.

parameters.name: $top
parameters.description: Number of records to return.

parameters.name: $skip
parameters.description: Number of records to skip.

parameters.name: $orderby
parameters.description: OData order by query option.

parameters.name: api-version
parameters.description: Version of the API to be used with the client request.

parameters.name: subscriptionId
parameters.description: Subscription credentials which uniquely identify Microsoft Azure subscription. The subscription ID forms part of the URI for every service call.

200.description: Lists a collection of Report record.

count.description: Total record count number across all pages.

apiTimeAvg.description: Average time it took to process request.

apiTimeMax.description: Maximum time it took to process request.

apiTimeMin.description: Minimum time it took to process request.

cacheHitCount.description: Number of times when content was served from cache policy.

cacheMissCount.description: Number of times content was fetched from backend.

callCountBlocked.description: Number of calls blocked due to invalid credentials. This includes calls returning HttpStatusCode.Unauthorized and HttpStatusCode.Forbidden and HttpStatusCode.TooManyRequests

callCountFailed.description: Number of calls failed due to proxy or backend errors. This includes calls returning HttpStatusCode.BadRequest(400) and any Code between HttpStatusCode.InternalServerError (500) and 600

callCountSuccess.description: Number of successful calls. This includes calls returning HttpStatusCode <= 301 and HttpStatusCode.NotModified and HttpStatusCode.TemporaryRedirect

country.description: Country to which this record data is related.

interval.description: Length of aggregation period.  Interval must be multiple of 15 minutes and may not be zero. The value should be in ISO 8601 format (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601#Durations).

name.description: Name depending on report endpoint specifies product, API, operation or developer name.

region.description: Country region to which this record data is related.

serviceTimeAvg.description: Average time it took to process request on backend.

serviceTimeMax.description: Maximum time it took to process request on backend.

serviceTimeMin.description: Minimum time it took to process request on backend.

timestamp.description: Start of aggregation period. The date conforms to the following format: `yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ssZ` as specified by the ISO 8601 standard.

zip.description: Zip code to which this record data is related.

200.description: Lists a collection of Report record.

count.description: Total record count number across all pages.

apiRegion.description: Azure region where the gateway that processed this request is located.

apiTime.description: The total time it took to process this request.

backendResponseCode.description: The HTTP status code received by the gateway as a result of forwarding this request to the backend.

cache.description: Specifies if response cache was involved in generating the response. If the value is none, the cache was not used. If the value is hit, cached response was returned. If the value is miss, the cache was used but lookup resulted in a miss and request was fulfilled by the backend.

ipAddress.description: The client IP address associated with this request.

method.description: The HTTP method associated with this request..

responseCode.description: The HTTP status code returned by the gateway.

responseSize.description: The size of the response returned by the gateway.

serviceTime.description: he time it took to forward this request to the backend and get the response back.

timestamp.description: The date and time when this request was received by the gateway in ISO 8601 format.

url.description: The full URL associated with this request.
